<p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: If you have Pivotal Application Service (PAS) installed, Pivotal recommends installing PKS on a separate instance of Ops Manager v2.0. For information about the impact of BOSH DNS on PKS, see the <a href="requirements.html#ops-man">Ops Manager v2.0</a> section of the <em>Prerequisites and Resource Requirements</em> topic.</p>

##<a id='workflows'></a> Workflows

###<a id='vsphere'></a> vSphere

If you want to install PKS on vSphere <strong>with</strong> NSX-T integration, use the following workflow:

* Consult the requirements in the [PKS with NSX-T Integration](requirements.html) section of <em>Prerequisites and Resource Requirements</em>.
* Perform the procedures in [Preparing to Deploy PKS on vSphere](preparing-vsphere.html).
* Perform the procedures in [Installing and Configuring PKS with NSX-T Integration](installing-nsx-t.html). 

If you want to install PKS on vSphere <strong>without</strong> NSX-T integration, use the following workflow:

* Consult the [Prerequisites and Resource Requirements](requirements.html) topic.
* Perform the procedures in [Preparing to Deploy PKS on vSphere](preparing-vsphere.html).
* Perform the procedures in [Installing and Configuring PKS](installing.html). 

If you want to use Harbor to store and manage container images, see the VMware Harbor Registry [documentation](https://docs.pivotal.io/partners/vmware-harbor).

###<a id='gcp'></a> GCP

If you want to install PKS on GCP, use the following workflow:

* Consult the [Prerequisites and Resource Requirements](requirements.html) topic.
* Perform the procedures in [Preparing to Deploy PKS on GCP](preparing-gcp.html).
* Perform the procedures in [Installing and Configuring PKS](installing.html).









